# Go Backend Rules

For backend work, follow `AGENTS.md`, `SPECIFICATION.md`, `SPECIFICATION_UI.md` (where the REST API supports UI flows), and `ARCHITECTURE.md`.

- Keep backend, API, execution, discovery, and security logic in `Go`.
- Preserve clean boundaries between `api`, `app`, `domain`, `execution`, `discovery`, `storage`, `security`, `artifacts`, and `ydbops/adapter` code.
- Keep the REST API explicit and documented; the UI must be able to rely on public API behavior only.
- Model long-running installation behavior as persisted phases, tasks, checkpoints, and structured status, not ad hoc goroutine state.
- Prefer native `Go` integrations for SSH, file transfer, validation, and orchestration over shelling out.
- Keep secret redaction and role checks close to API and reporting boundaries.
- When behavior changes, anchor it to the relevant requirement IDs instead of copying spec text into code comments.
